University Database SQL Join Lab

Overview

This project demonstrates how to create and manage a University Database System using SQL. It includes the creation of four related tables: DEPARTMENT, STUDENT, COURSE, and ENROLLMENT, along with inserting sample data and running various SQL queries using JOIN, GROUP BY, HAVING, and aggregate functions.

The purpose of this project is to understand how relational databases work by linking multiple tables using Primary Keys and Foreign Keys, and retrieving meaningful information from them.

---

Database Name

"university_join_lab"

---

Tables Included

1. DEPARTMENT

Stores department information.

Column Name| Description
DeptID| Unique department ID
DeptName| Name of the department
Building| Department building name

---

2. STUDENT

Stores student details.

Column Name| Description
StudentID| Unique student ID
FullName| Student full name
DeptID| Department ID (Foreign Key)
Batch| Student batch
CGPA| Student CGPA

---

3. COURSE

Stores course information.

Column Name| Description
CourseID| Unique course ID
CourseTitle| Name of the course
Credit| Course credit
DeptID| Department ID (Foreign Key)

---

4. ENROLLMENT

Stores student enrollment information.

Column Name| Description
EnrollID| Unique enrollment ID
StudentID| Student ID (Foreign Key)
CourseID| Course ID (Foreign Key)
Semester| Semester name
Marks| Student marks

---

Features

This project includes SQL queries to:

- Display student names with department names
- Show student course enrollments and marks
- List all students, including those without enrollments
- List all courses, including courses without students
- Count students department-wise
- Count enrollments course-wise
- Calculate average, maximum, and minimum marks for each course
- Show each student’s average marks and total enrolled courses
- Display top-performing students
- Filter students by marks range
- Search student names using patterns

