Purpose of the Project

The main goal of this project is to practice SQL JOIN operations and understand how data can be connected between multiple tables.

It helps learners understand:

- How to build a relational database
- How to maintain relationships between tables
- How to retrieve related data using JOINs
- How to summarize and filter data using SQL functions

This kind of database system can be used in educational institutions to manage student records, courses, departments, and enrollment data.

---

Expected Outcome

After completing this project, users will be able to:

- Create relational database tables
- Connect tables using foreign keys
- Perform SQL JOIN operations
- Analyze data with aggregate functions
- Write efficient SQL queries for real-world scenarios

---

Conclusion

This project is a simple but effective implementation of a University Database Management System using SQL. It demonstrates how to organize academic data in multiple related tables and how to retrieve useful information through SQL queries.

It is a practical exercise for learning database design, table relationships, and SQL query operations.
